00:00:39,260 --> 00:00:42,460
invariant under the various transformations that you

11
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:43,280
might want to do.

12
00:00:43,980 --> 00:00:45,400
An example of the structure

13
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,820
that can be on a space,

14
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:49,540
if you know anything about curved

15
00:00:49,540 --> 00:00:52,060
spaces and differential geometry and so forth,

16
00:00:52,060 --> 00:00:54,340
the metric structure of certain,

17
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:54,940
of metrical

18
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:55,340
spaces.

19
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:57,430
The spaces of Riemann spaces are

20
00:00:57,430 --> 00:00:59,520
part of the structure of those spaces.

21
00:01:00,140 --> 00:01:02,940
They're characterized by a metric on the space,

22
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:04,980
a distance formula between neighboring

23
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:05,480
points.

24
00:01:07,682 --> 00:01:07,802
對

25
00:01:08,962 --> 00:01:11,742
Poisson structures are different than metric structures.

26
00:01:12,062 --> 00:01:13,242
They're more abstract.

27
00:01:14,002 --> 00:01:17,672
And they were invented largely to describe

28
00:01:17,672 --> 00:01:21,342
