29
00:01:21,942 --> 00:01:24,512
Its properties under transformations

30
00:01:24,512 --> 00:01:27,082
which change the coordinates.

31
00:01:27,342 --> 00:01:27,482
Now,

32
00:01:27,482 --> 00:01:29,072
the coordinates of a phase

33
00:01:29,072 --> 00:01:30,662
space are not just the q's.

34
00:01:31,022 --> 00:01:32,652
The coordinates of a phase space

35
00:01:32,652 --> 00:01:34,282
are the q's and the p's.

36
00:01:34,282 --> 00:01:35,822
And roughly speaking,

37
00:01:35,822 --> 00:01:36,302
the question,

38
00:01:36,302 --> 00:01:39,011
the kind of question that you might ask is

39
00:01:39,011 --> 00:01:41,721
what are the various transformations that you can do?

40
00:01:41,802 --> 00:01:42,262
For example,

41
00:01:42,262 --> 00:01:45,652
that mix up p's and q's that

42
00:01:45,652 --> 00:01:49,042
preserve the basic structure of classical mechanics.

43
00:01:50,502 --> 00:01:51,262
As I said,

44
00:01:51,262 --> 00:01:52,582
this is the kind of question,

45
00:01:52,582 --> 00:01:54,082
the kind of structural question,

46
00:01:54,082 --> 00:01:56,782
the kind of formal question that the

47
00:01:56,782 --> 00:01:59,482
French mathematicians were awfully damn good at.

48
00:02:00,442 --> 00:02:02,002
It turned out to be very

49
00:02:02,002 --> 00:02:03,562
important to the future of physics.

50
00:02:04,282 --> 00:02:05,352
It wasn't the French who

51
00:02:05,352 --> 00:02:06,422
figured out why it was important.

52
00:02:06,562 --> 00:02:08,312
It was the French who

53
00:02:08,312 --> 00:02:10,062
figured out how the basic structure,

54
00:02:10,062 --> 00:02:12,942
the French and Hamilton basically,

55
00:02:12,942 --> 00:02:14,552
who figured out what the

56
00:02:14,552 --> 00:02:16,162
structure of classical mechanics is.

57
00:02:18,581 --> 00:02:22,302
And it got more and more abstract.

58
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:25,062
The most concrete version was,

59
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:25,402
of course,

60
00:02:25,402 --> 00:02:26,162
Newton's version.

61
00:02:27,622 --> 00:02:29,322
The most abstract version,

62
00:02:29,322 --> 00:02:31,002
I don't know how abstract it is.

